In case you didn’t know, I had the amazing opportunity of being the consultant for Team Brazil Coed Elite and Team Brazil Junior Coed Advance for 2022 Pan American Championship & 2023 ICU World Championship 

Coed Elite was who I initially signed up to work with. Coaches @satoristunt @luizabrasiel did a fantastic job coaching and I couldn’t have been more proud of them two! Our goal was top three since Team Brazil has never reach the podium and anything less was a failure. After day 1 we were sitting in second by 5 points and had plenty of room for improvement to be even better day 2. Day two was a hit routine but not nearly as good as day 1 so we left room for others to sneak in. Gladly it was enough to stay top 3 and was able to take home Team Brazil first ever Coed Elite medal. Team Australia and Team Japan were better on that day. Next year you know what to do!!

Juco!!! What they didn’t know was I originally said NO to working with them. I’m glad I had a change of heart 💚. @jacadami and Zeca were amazing with coaching them and taking my advice on certain areas. After day 1 Juco was in 4th but only because of a legality which would of placed them in 1st. Day 2 JUCO put on a show and ended up placing 2nd in the world taking home the first ever silver medal for Team Brazil Junior Coed 🥈Tio VonVon was incredibly proud!!

What a ride it was and the relationships built were what made it all worth it!! Thanks @cbcdoficial  for trusting me to help bring the vision to light!!

Finally the time has come!!! 

This year was definitely one for the books, so many individuals have helped make it incredible. @teamchowchoreo for 2 amazing routines, @spirit_vibe for fire music as always!! 

The sophomores and super sophomores for putting your all into the program!!! The WEENIES for pushing pass barriers that at first seemed to trouble them.

TVCC sports and Administration for always striving to be the best and supporting the cheer team. The rookies for trusting the process and finding your why!! 

Coach @franklintvcc for always being there to help mentor and deliver advice!! Lastly, coach @mollybreanne for jumping in and understanding how to take over when needed. I was extremely proud to be your coach and even more proud to coach along side you!! First year and you’re already a GRAND CHAMP!! The future is bright in the VALLEY, RUN IT BACK ❤️ 🖤
